# Changing CSS üé®

You can modify the style of an element using the `style` property.

```javascript
const element = document.getElementById("p1");
element.style.color = "blue";
element.style.fontSize = "24px";
```
(Note: CSS property `font-size` becomes camelCase `fontSize` in JS.)

# Changing Attributes üè∑Ô∏è

You can get or set HTML attributes.

```javascript
const img = document.getElementById("myImage");

// Change the source of an image
img.src = "landscape.jpg";

// Or use setAttribute
img.setAttribute("alt", "New description");
```

# DOM Nodes üå≤

You can add or remove elements dynamically.

## Create
```javascript
const para = document.createElement("p");
para.innerText = "This is new.";
document.body.appendChild(para);
```

## Remove
```javascript
const elm = document.getElementById("p1");
elm.remove();
```
